                                has made enormous strides in combating desertification in
                                the biologically diverse but threatened Caucasus region. More
                                than 5,700,000 trees have been planted and restored, and
                                hundreds of jobs have been created for Armenians in seasonal
                                tree-related programs. Forests, community planting sites, and
                                backyard nurseries span throughout the entire country,
                                preserving Armenia’s natural resources. ATP’s Environmental
